- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is another possible category as the paper discusses the implications of the findings on urban planning and transportation policies. 
- cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) is a possible category as the paper analyzes human mobility patterns and spatial interactions from a social and behavioral perspective. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is a possible category as the paper may involve database management and analysis techniques for the check-in data set.
